{
  "texts": [
    "Without such alignment, naive aggregation leads to spatial inconsistencies, degrading the quality of temporally accumulated features in a stream-based manner.",
    "Inspired by [10], we transform the spatial coordinates of the previous voxel grid P e (t -1) into the current ego-centric coordinate as:Pe (t) = T t g→e • T t-1 e→g • P e (t -1),(1)where T t-1 e→g maps coordinates from the past ego frame to the global frame, and T t g→e brings them to the current egocentric frame.",
    "We compute the warped voxel feature as:V t warp (P e (t)) = Interp(V t-1 fin, Pe (t)),(2)where Interp(•) denotes trilinear interpolation that maps past features to the current frame while preserving spatial consistency.Voxel Feature Refinement.",
    "The warping process propagates contextual cues from past observations, but it inevitably introduces distortions due to the interpolation mechanism, particularly in empty regions, at object boundaries, and in crowded areas.",
    "These distortions can lead to erroneous values or blurred object contours, degrading feature quality and temporal consistency."
  ]
}